Malaysia Monitoring Inflation ‘Very Carefully,’ Governor Says

-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-04-05T03:02:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/malaysia-monitoring-inflation-very-carefully-governor-says.html
Zeti Akhtar Aziz,  Malaysia ’s central
bank governor, comments on inflation and  interest rates . She
made these remarks to reporters in Kuala Lumpur today.  The central bank maintained its benchmark overnight
interest rate at 2.75 percent on March 11, while ordering
lenders to set aside more cash as reserves. Policy makers are
next scheduled to meet on May 5.  On inflation:  “We have to monitor very carefully first the nature of the
inflation, whether it is demand-driven or whether it is due to
supply factors, and also whether it is temporary or a more
permanent trend. All these assessments will have to be made.  Also assessment will be made to the risks to growth and the
extent that our monetary policy the degree of the accommodation
that needs to be given to support this growth. All these factors
will be taken into consideration and we will have a monetary
policy meeting in May and we will make known our assessment.”  On whether rates may be raised:
“We will gather the information and make the assessment at that
point in time.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
